Program:
    pageRank.py

Usage:
    python3 pageRank.py <filename> <dataset_type> [undirected]

Dataset types:
    football
    normal

Example uses:
    python3 pageRank.py NCAA_football.csv football
    python3 pageRank.py dolphins.csv normal
    python3 pageRank.py lesmis.csv normal
    python3 pageRank.py dolphinsDir.csv normal undirected
    python3 pageRank.py lesmisDir.csv normal undirected

Notes:
    For NCAA football, edges point from loser to winner.
    For normal datasets, each row is treated as node1 -> node2.
    We chose to use the optional undirected flag for files that list each undirected edge only once.
    For large datasets, example input to print to file:
    python3 pageRank.py NCAA_football.csv football > football_output.txt
    Preset damping factor is 0.85, tolerance is 0.0001, and max iterations is 1000.
